 philosophy, humanities, and social sciences, especially psychology. Also, the apparent cacophony of extant interpretations of these two concepts is explained as the inevitable and even useful result of the polysemy inherent to all common-sense concepts, in line with the understanding of concepts developed by M. Polanyi in the 20th century. Thus, a thorough, nuanced grasp of their complex mutual relationship is established, and many platitudes affecting today's received views, and scholarship, are cast aside.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 4aGrausamkeit. 4aHumor. 4aParadox. 4aSex. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aCruelty.  ahumour.  aparadox.  asex.1 aArnarsson, Ársæll Már, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831107600190 cprintz978311075976140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075983940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110759839423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110759839/original  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPHb2022